{"id": "1ccadca5-4048-44ce-b274-e4727fd0e371", "task_id": "ac9f7c2f-da5c-4d8f-aaf8-eb44341da3f7", "path": "backend/templates/index.html", "artifact_type": "file", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>CYBERPUNK LOGIN_INTERFACE // ACCESS GRANTED</title>\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Orbitron:wght@400;700&family=Share+Tech+Mono&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <style>\n        :root {\n            --primary-neon: #00ffff; /* Cyan */\n            --secondary-neon: #ff00ff; /* Magenta */\n            --tertiary-neon: #00ff00; /* Green */\n            --dark-bg: #1a0a2c; /* Dark violet */\n            --medium-bg: #2a1040;\n            --input-bg: #11071d;\n            --text-color: #e0e0e0;\n            --error-color: #ff3366;\n            --success-color: #00ff99;\n        }\n\n        *, *::before, *::after {\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;\n            background-color: var(--dark-bg);\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: center;\n            align-items: center;\n            min-height: 100vh;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            position: relative;\n            /* Background grid/dots */\n            background-image: \n                linear-gradient(to right, rgba(0,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px),\n                linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,255,255,0.05) 1px, transparent 1px);\n            background-size: 50px 50px;\n        }\n\n        body::before {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: \n                radial-gradient(circle at center, transparent 0%, transparent 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 100%);\n            pointer-events: none;\n            z-index: -1;\n        }\n\n        .login-container {\n            background-color: var(--medium-bg);\n            border: 2px solid var(--primary-neon);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--primary-neon), inset 0 0 10px var(--primary-neon);\n            padding: 40px 30px;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            text-align: center;\n            width: 100%;\n            max-width: 400px;\n            position: relative;\n            animation: pulse-border 2s infinite alternate;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes pulse-border {\n            0% { box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--primary-neon), inset 0 0 10px var(--primary-neon); }\n            100% { box-shadow: 0 0 35px var(--secondary-neon), inset 0 0 15px var(--secondary-neon); }\n        }\n\n        h1 {\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            color: var(--tertiary-neon);\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            font-size: 2.2em;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--tertiary-neon), 0 0 20px var(--tertiary-neon);\n            letter-spacing: 2px;\n            position: relative;\n        }\n\n        h1::before, h1::after {\n            content: attr(data-text);\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            color: var(--primary-neon);\n            text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--primary-neon);\n            overflow: hidden;\n            animation: glitch 2s linear infinite alternate;\n        }\n\n        h1::after {\n            left: 2px;\n            text-shadow: -2px 0 var(--secondary-neon);\n            animation: glitch 2.5s linear infinite alternate-reverse;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes glitch {\n            0% { clip-path: inset(0 0 95% 0); transform: translateX(0px); }\n            20% { clip-path: inset(60% 0 0 0); transform: translateX(-5px); }\n            40% { clip-path: inset(0 0 50% 0); transform: translateX(5px); }\n            60% { clip-path: inset(70% 0 0 0); transform: translateX(-2px); }\n            80% { clip-path: inset(0 0 10% 0); transform: translateX(3px); }\n            100% { clip-path: inset(0 0 95% 0); transform: translateX(0px); }\n        }\n\n        .form-group {\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            text-align: left;\n        }\n\n        label {\n            display: block;\n            margin-bottom: 8px;\n            color: var(--primary-neon);\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0,255,255,0.5);\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"],\n        input[type=\"password\"] {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 12px 15px;\n            background-color: var(--input-bg);\n            border: 1px solid var(--primary-neon);\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            font-size: 1em;\n            transition: all 0.3s ease;\n            box-shadow: inset 0 0 5px rgba(0,255,255,0.3);\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"]:focus,\n        input[type=\"password\"]:focus {\n            outline: none;\n            border-color: var(--secondary-neon);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--secondary-neon), inset 0 0 5px var(--secondary-neon);\n            background-color: #200d30;\n        }\n\n        input::placeholder {\n            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);\n            opacity: 0.7;\n        }\n\n        button {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 14px;\n            background-color: var(--tertiary-neon);\n            color: var(--dark-bg);\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            font-size: 1.1em;\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            letter-spacing: 1px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 15px var(--tertiary-neon);\n        }\n\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: var(--primary-neon);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 25px var(--primary-neon), inset 0 0 10px var(--primary-neon);\n            transform: translateY(-2px);\n        }\n\n        button:active {\n            transform: translateY(0);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--primary-neon);\n        }\n\n        .message-area {\n            margin-top: 25px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            word-break: break-all;\n            background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);\n            border: 1px solid transparent;\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            min-height: 40px;\n            display: flex;\n            align-items: center;\n            justify-content: center;\n        }\n\n        .message-area.error {\n            color: var(--error-color);\n            border-color: var(--error-color);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--error-color);\n        }\n\n        .message-area.success {\n            color: var(--success-color);\n            border-color: var(--success-color);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--success-color);\n        }\n\n        /* Placeholder for a \"terminal\" like effect with JS if needed later */\n        .terminal-output {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            background-color: #0d0d0d;\n            border: 1px solid var(--tertiary-neon);\n            padding: 15px;\n            font-size: 0.85em;\n            color: var(--tertiary-neon);\n            text-align: left;\n            white-space: pre-wrap;\n            max-height: 150px;\n            overflow-y: auto;\n            box-shadow: inset 0 0 5px rgba(0,255,0,0.5);\n            display: none; /* Hidden by default */\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 600px) {\n            .login-container {\n                margin: 20px;\n                padding: 30px 20px;\n            }\n            h1 {\n                font-size: 1.8em;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"login-container\">\n        <h1 data-text=\"ACCESS_GRID\">ACCESS_GRID</h1>\n        <form action=\"/login\" method=\"POST\" id=\"loginForm\">\n            <div class=\"form-group\">\n                <label for=\"username\">[[ USERNAME ]]</label>\n                <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" placeholder=\"Enter your neural ID\" required autocomplete=\"username\">\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"form-group\">\n                <label for=\"password\">[[ PASSWORD ]]</label>\n                <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" placeholder=\"Enter your secure key\" required autocomplete=\"current-password\">\n            </div>\n            <button type=\"submit\">LOG_IN // INITIATE_SESSION</button>\n        </form>\n        <div class=\"message-area\" id=\"responseMessage\">\n            <!-- Backend response message will be displayed here -->\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        // This script will capture the backend response and display it.\n        // Note: The form submission itself is handled by the browser as a standard POST request.\n        // If the backend returns a successful JSON response, the browser will navigate to a page\n        // displaying that JSON. If the backend returns HTML, it will render it.\n        // To *intercept* the response for dynamic display without page reload,\n        // one would typically use fetch API. However, the task explicitly states\n        // 'DO NOT use event.preventDefault() blocking actual form submission. Always use standard HTML',\n        // meaning we should allow the browser's default form submission behavior.\n        //\n        // Therefore, this JS section will primarily serve as a placeholder or\n        // for very basic client-side enhancements that don't prevent default submission.\n        // For example, if you wanted to clear a message area after a few seconds *after* page load.\n\n        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n            const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);\n            const status = urlParams.get('status');\n            const message = urlParams.get('message');\n            const responseMessageDiv = document.getElementById('responseMessage');\n\n            if (status && message) {\n                responseMessageDiv.textContent = decodeURIComponent(message);\n                if (status === 'success') {\n                    responseMessageDiv.classList.add('success');\n                } else if (status === 'error') {\n                    responseMessageDiv.classList.add('error');\n                }\n                // Optionally, clear the message after some time, or the next form interaction\n                setTimeout(() => {\n                    responseMessageDiv.textContent = '';\n                    responseMessageDiv.className = 'message-area';\n                    // Remove parameters from URL if desired to avoid re-display on refresh\n                    history.replaceState({}, document.title, window.location.pathname);\n                }, 5000);\n            }\n\n            // This part is for potential future dynamic updates if requirements change\n            // and client-side handling of backend JSON response is introduced.\n            // As per current critical requirement, default form submission is used.\n            // If the backend were to return JSON that the frontend should interpret,\n            // an event listener on submit with fetch API would be needed.\n            // Example if fetch was allowed (commented out due to instruction):\n            /*\n            const loginForm = document.getElementById('loginForm');\n            loginForm.addEventListener('submit', async (event) => {\n                // If event.preventDefault() was allowed:\n                // event.preventDefault();\n\n                // const username = document.getElementById('username').value;\n                // const password = document.getElementById('password').value;\n\n                // try {\n                //     const response = await fetch('/login', {\n                //         method: 'POST',\n                //         headers: {\n                //             'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n                //         },\n                //         body: JSON.stringify({ username, password }),\n                //     });\n\n                //     const data = await response.json();\n\n                //     if (response.ok) {\n                //         responseMessageDiv.textContent = data.message || 'Login successful!';\n                //         responseMessageDiv.classList.remove('error');\n                //         responseMessageDiv.classList.add('success');\n                //     } else {\n                //         responseMessageDiv.textContent = data.detail || 'Login failed.';\n                //         responseMessageDiv.classList.remove('success');\n                //         responseMessageDiv.classList.add('error');\n                //     }\n                // } catch (error) {\n                //     console.error('Network or server error:', error);\n                //     responseMessageDiv.textContent = 'Connection error. Please try again.';\n                //     responseMessageDiv.classList.remove('success');\n                //     responseMessageDiv.classList.add('error');\n                // }\n            });\n            */\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n", "patches": [], "metadata": {"language": "html", "framework": "static_html", "explanation": "This `index.html` file creates a cyberpunk-themed login page. It uses standard HTML5 for structure, CSS3 for styling, and minimal Vanilla JavaScript for handling potential URL-based messages after a form submission. The design features a dark background, neon accents (cyan, magenta, green), a futuristic 'Orbitron' font for the title, and a 'Share Tech Mono' font for general text, giving it a terminal-like appearance.\n\nKey features include:\n- **Cyberpunk Aesthetic**: Achieved through color palette, fonts, text shadows for neon glow, and a subtle glitch effect on the main title.\n- **Login Form**: A standard HTML `<form>` element configured to `POST` data to the `/login` endpoint, as required by the backend. It includes input fields for username and password with appropriate `name` attributes for backend processing.\n- **Responsive Design**: Basic media queries are included to ensure the layout is presentable on smaller screens.\n- **Message Area**: A `div` with `id=\"responseMessage\"` is provided to display messages. The accompanying JavaScript snippet is designed to read `status` and `message` query parameters from the URL (e.g., if the backend redirects with them after processing a login attempt) and display them with appropriate styling, then clear them after a short delay. This adheres to the critical requirement of *not* preventing default form submission and letting the browser handle the POST request.", "dependencies": []}, "created_at": "2026-05-17 15:23:09.039229"}